    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Matthew",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "John the Baptist preaches in Jud\u00e6a\u2014Jesus is baptized, and the Father acclaims Him as His Beloved Son.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "In those days came John the Baptist, preaching in the wilderness of Jud\u00e6a,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:72.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And saying, Repent ye: for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "The Greek word denotes \u201ca change of heart or mind,\u201d i.e., \u201ca conversion.\u201d Alma 7:9; 9:25 (25\u201326); Hel. 5:32; D&C 33:10.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 10:9. TG\u00a0Kingdom of God, in Heaven; Kingdom of God, on Earth.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0has come. Isa. 56:1; Matt. 4:17; D&C 39:19.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For this is he that was spoken of by the prophet Esaias, saying, The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "See JST\u00a0Luke 3:4\u201311 (Appendix). TG\u00a0Foreordination.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 40:3; Mark 1:3; Luke 3:4; John 1:23; D&C 65:3; 88:66.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 10:8 (7\u201310); D&C 34:6; 65:1 (1\u20132); 84:26.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 115
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 7:19 (9, 19).",
                        "start": 149,
                        "end": 154
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1190
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the same John had his raiment of camel's hair, and a leathern girdle about his loins; and his meat was locusts and wild honey.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0garment. See also 2\u00a0Kgs. 1:8.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 13:4.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 11:22.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then went out to him Jerusalem, and all Jud\u00e6a, and all the region round about Jordan,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And were baptized of him in Jordan, confessing their sins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Confession.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees come to his baptism, he said unto them, O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "See JST\u00a0Matt. 9:18\u201321 (Appendix). Luke 7:29 (29\u201330).",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0crop of serpents. Matt. 12:34; 23:33; Alma 9:8; 10:17 (17\u201325).",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Warn.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Bring forth therefore fruits meet for repentance:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 3:34\u201336 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0appropriate to, worthy of.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Qualifications for; Repent.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And think not to say within yourselves, We have Abraham to our father: for I say unto you, that God is able of these stones to raise up children unto Abraham.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees: therefore every tree which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:36 (36\u201341); 3\u00a0Ne. 14:19; D&C 52:18; 97:7.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 13:7; Jacob 5:42 (42\u201366).",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I indeed baptize you with water unto repentance: but he that cometh after me is mightier than I, whose shoes I am not worthy to bear: he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost, and with fire:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 3:38\u201340 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 19:3 (1\u20137); 2\u00a0Ne. 31:5 (5\u201310).",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Qualifications for.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "See JST\u00a0John 1:27\u201334 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worthiness.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Baptism of.",
                        "start": 143,
                        "end": 150
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 19:31.",
                        "start": 185,
                        "end": 189
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 180,
                        "end": 184
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whose fan is in his hand, and he will throughly purge his floor, and gather his wheat into the garner; but he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 51:2.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0storehouse.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 101
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 43:32; 63:34 (33\u201334); 101:66.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 155
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then cometh Jesus from Galilee to Jordan unto John, to be baptized of him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Baptism of.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p13",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But John forbad him, saying, I have need to be baptized of thee, and comest thou to me?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Jesus answering said unto him, Suffer it to be so now: for thus it becometh us to fulfil all righteousness. Then he suffered him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 3:43\u201346 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Permit it now.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0is fitting for us.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Essential.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Mission of; Righteousness.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Jesus, when he was baptized, went up straightway out of the water: and, lo, the heavens were opened unto him, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove, and lighting upon him:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism; Baptism, Immersion.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0immediately.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of.",
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 135
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Dove, Sign of.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 165
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And lo a voice from heaven, saying, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 9:7; Luke 9:35 (34\u201336). TG\u00a0God, Body of, Corporeal Nature; God, Manifestations of.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 17:5; 3\u00a0Ne. 11:7; JS\u2014H 1:17. TG\u00a0Witness of the Father.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godhead; God the Father, Elohim; Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}